    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix scheduling issue with open_bladerf_from_serial not being used\n\n### Summary\nThe BladeRF initialization code was not using the existing `open_bladerf_from_serial` function, causing missed scheduling opportunities when multiple BladeRF devices are connected. The code always opened the first available device instead of allowing specification of a specific device by serial number.\n\nThis fix enables proper device selection by using the serial number provided in the `sdr_addrs` configuration field.\n\n### Changes\n- `radio/BLADERF/bladerf_lib.c`: Modified `device_init` function to check for serial number in `sdr_addrs` and use `open_bladerf_from_serial` when provided\n- `radio/BLADERF/bladerf_lib.c`: Added proper error handling and memory cleanup\n- `radio/BLADERF/bladerf_lib.c`: Included `<string.h>` for `strlen` function\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen multiple BladeRF devices are connected and a specific device is intended to be used for a UE with pending data, the current implementation would open the first available device rather than the intended one. This leads to incorrect scheduling as the wrong device may be used for transmission/reception.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Connect multiple BladeRF devices to the system\n2. Configure OAI to use BladeRF without specifying a serial number\n3. Observe that the first enumerated device is always used regardless of which device was intended\n\nWith this fix, users can specify the device serial in their configuration:\n```\ndevice = {\n    name = \"bladerf\";\n    sdr_addrs = \"serial_number_here\";\n};\n```\nThis ensures the correct device is selected for scheduling.\n"
}